        <p>Laguna Niguel splits cleanly into two appliance markets, and understanding which one you're in determines how we approach your repair.</p>

        <p>The estate neighborhoods &mdash; Bear Brand Ranch, Rancho Niguel, parts of Monarch Summit &mdash; have luxury kitchens with Sub-Zero 48-inch built-in refrigerators, Wolf 60-inch ranges, Thermador column freezers, Miele dishwashers, and built-in wine storage. These are high-value appliances where OEM parts aren't optional &mdash; an aftermarket compressor in a Sub-Zero voids the manufacturer's goodwill and often fails within 18 months. We carry genuine parts for all of these brands on every vehicle.</p>

        <p>The condo and townhome neighborhoods &mdash; Marina Hills, Beacon Hill, Kingswood, parts of Sulphur Creek &mdash; have Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, KitchenAid, and GE appliances. These units are more price-sensitive to repair, and honesty about repair-vs-replace economics matters more. A 12-year-old Samsung washer with a failed spider arm might cost more to repair than to replace. We'll tell you that directly, show you the math, and let you decide.</p>

        <p>Hard water affects both markets equally. The mineral content in the 92677 water supply causes inlet valve calcification, spray arm blockages, and ice maker line restrictions across all brands. We check for hard water damage on every relevant call in Laguna Niguel.</p>

